    <h1 class="display-4">Biography of Hugh Everett</h1>
    <img src="~/hugh-everett-bio.jpg" alt="Hugh Everett" />
    <p>Hugh Everett III (1930-1982) was an American physicist best known for his contributions to the field of quantum mechanics. Born in Washington, D.C., he displayed exceptional mathematical talent from an early age.</p>

    <p>Everett's groundbreaking work on the Many-Worlds Interpretation of quantum mechanics set him apart in the world of physics. This interpretation suggests that every quantum event branches into multiple, non-communicating parallel universes, creating a vast multiverse.</p>
